\[\frac{\begin{pmatrix} 2 \\ -6 \\ 6 \end{pmatrix} \cdot \begin{pmatrix} 1 \\ -3 \\ 3 \end{pmatrix}}{\begin{pmatrix} 1 \\ -3 \\ 3 \end{pmatrix} \cdot \begin{pmatrix} 1 \\ -3 \\ 3 \end{pmatrix}} \begin{pmatrix} 1 \\ -3 \\ 3 \end{pmatrix} = \frac{-12}{19} \begin{pmatrix} 1 \\ -3 \\ 3 \end{pmatrix}.\]Thus, the distance between the planes is $\left| \frac{-12}{19} \right| \cdot \frac{8 - 0}{\sqrt{1^2 + (-3)^2 + 3^2}} = \boxed{\frac{24}{19}}.$

