The projection of $\begin{pmatrix} -10 \\ 0 \\ 0 \end{pmatrix}$ onto $\begin{pmatrix} 0 \\ 1 \\ -1 \end{pmatrix}$ is
\[\operatorname{proj}_{\begin{pmatrix} 0 \\ 1 \\ -1 \end{pmatrix}} \begin{pmatrix} -10 \\ 0 \\ 0 \end{pmatrix} = \frac{\begin{pmatrix} -10 \\ 0 \\ 0 \end{pmatrix} \cdot \begin{pmatrix} 0 \\ 1 \\ -1 \end{pmatrix}}{\begin{pmatrix} 0 \\ 1 \\ -1 \end{pmatrix} \cdot \begin{pmatrix} 0 \\ 1 \\ -1 \end{pmatrix}} \begin{pmatrix} 0 \\ 1 \\ -1 \end{pmatrix} = \begin{pmatrix} 0 \\ 0 \\ 0 \end{pmatrix}.\]Thus, the distance between the planes is $\boxed{6}.$

